MBOMBELA &#8211; While the rain continues, a man was rescued from drowning in the city this morning.The man was rescued from a river behind the Pick n Pay centre.According to Bossies Community Justice&#8217;s (BCJ) Mr Danie Theron, members of the Nelspruit fire department managed to rescue the man from the river. ER24 branch manager Mr Greg Wilcox said the man was believed to be in his forties.LifeMed medical services transported the man to Rob Ferreira hospital. An eyewitness to the incident stated that the man was apparently discharged from the hospital&#8217;s psychiatric ward yesterday.READ MORE: Son s tragic drowning plunges family into turmoil&nbsp;